Reasoning: The paper discusses software engineering principles and practices for version control and change management in scientific applications. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as it deals with software development processes. cs.CE (Computational Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are also relevant as they deal with software development and programming. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is relevant as it deals with managing and preserving digital data, which is important in scientific applications. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as it deals with designing user interfaces for software applications, which is important for usability of scientific applications.
